  <body><![CDATA[Oh, man. You're so right about <i>Doonesbury</i>. It's truly hella WICKED brilliant. And quite possibly a timeless classic despite its topical nature, because of the immensely creative way Trudeau presents everything. His disembodied "all hat no cattle" depiction of Bush that eventually morphed into the dented Roman helmet?! OH MUH GAW. *heart snorgle heart heart snorgle*<br /><br />You have a point, guys. Apples &amp; orangutans. Although I do think it's a healthy exercise to compare and contrast acknowledged monoliths of any medium to less acclaimed/groundbreaking works. <br /><br />But yeah, I think we're getting into semantics, and I wholeheartedly appreciate all the titles being mentioned, so I'll concede. The funny pages aren't such a wasteland after all. :)]]></body>
  
